-- I’ll Have Another Will Be Retired From Racing, Trainer Says
-- B y   M a s o n   L e v i n s o n   a n d   E b e n   N o v y - W i l l i a m s
-- 2012-06-08T17:20:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-08/i-ll-have-another-will-be-retired-from-racing-trainer-says.html
I’ll Have Another won’t race again
after being scratched from the Belmont Stakes and missing a
chance to complete thoroughbred racing’s first Triple Crown in
34 years, the colt’s owner and trainer said.  The 3-year-old chestnut was pulled out of the Belmont today
because of tendinitis in his front left leg.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Larry Siddons at 
 lsiddons@bloomberg.net  